        static Range getRangeByAddress(String cellReferences,
                               Cell cellContext,
                               Workbook wbk)
        to get a range by giving the cell reference (for example: 'worksheet1!A1B1:A2B2;worksheet2!A1C1:A3C2'),an object of cell class and a Workbook object
        Parameters:
        cellReferences - cell reference (for example: 'worksheet1!A1B1:A2B2;worksheet2!A1C1:A3C2')
        cellContext - a object with cell reference
        wbk - is the object of the workbook that contains the cell within the cell reference

        an object of the Range class.
